                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d492">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.50 Recovery/6–2948: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-06-29T20:00:00-04:00"
                            >June 29, 1948—8 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>953. As indicated previous telegrams, Dept and ECA quite agreeable deletion
                    “direct supervision and control” Article IV and Embassy authorized finalize
                    language this article as proposed Embassy 1178 June 29. (Sent Nanking as 951,
                    Rptd Shanghai as 1173.)</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Marshall</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
